name: President Biden
tweet: There’s no time to waste when it comes to the existential threat of climate change. That’s why I’ve set a bold new goal of cutting U.S. greenhouse gas emissions at least in half by 2030.

name: President Biden
tweet: From the moment we took office, my Administration has been working around the clock to get America vaccinated quickly and equitably.  Here’s a breakdown of our progress:  https://t.co/2kxSimaWQc

name: President Biden
tweet: No one should be denied a roof over their head simply because of their gender identity. Today, @HUDgov took action to make that clear.

name: President Biden
tweet: To all the states, cities, tribal nations, businesses, and organizations that stepped up the past four years to lead on tackling climate change: thank you.    Today we announced a new national target and from here on out, you’ll have a partner in me and my Administration.

name: President Biden
tweet: We’ve officially passed 200 million shots since the start of our Administration. It’s a big milestone, but we still have a long way to go. Get vaccinated, folks.  https://t.co/EgRIlGQKlV

name: President Biden
tweet: I applaud the Senate and the Congressional Asian Pacific American Caucus for passing the COVID-19 Hate Crimes Act — and for bringing us closer to achieving justice and equality for the AAPI community.  Acts of hate against Asian Americans are wrong, un-American, and must stop.

name: President Biden
tweet: No nation can solve the climate crisis on our own — all of us have to step up. Today’s Leaders Summit on Climate is our first step to set our world on a path to a secure, prosperous, and sustainable future.   Time is short, but I believe that we can and will do this.  https://t.co/t49hfXdkEd

name: President Biden
tweet: Today, we officially reached our goal of 200 million shots in my first 100 days.   Make no mistake: This is an American achievement. It’s a powerful demonstration of unity and resolve. And a reminder of what we can accomplish when we come together in pursuit of a common goal.

name: President Biden
tweet: America is back. We rejoined the Paris Agreement and are ready to rally the world to tackle the climate crisis. Let’s do this.

name: President Biden
tweet: The signs are unmistakable. The science is undeniable. The costs of inaction keep mounting.   The United States isn’t waiting — we are resolved to take action to combat climate change.

name: President Biden
tweet: When I think of climate change, I think about jobs.    Within our climate response lies an extraordinary engine of job creation ready to be fired up.

name: President Biden
tweet: This Earth Day, I’m proud to say science is back.

name: President Biden
tweet: Today I’m bringing together leaders from around the world to meet this moment of climate peril, and extraordinary opportunity. No nation can solve this crisis on its own, and this summit is a step on a path to a secure, prosperous, and sustainable future.  https://t.co/lcUUsgyEo3

name: President Biden
tweet: We’re making incredible progress when it comes to beating COVID-19. But in this moment, we can’t just rebuild to the way things were before the pandemic — we have to build back better.   That’s exactly what the American Jobs Plan does.

name: President Biden
tweet: Congratulations to Vanita Gupta on making history as the first woman of color to serve as Associate Attorney General. Now, I urge the Senate to confirm Kristen Clarke. Both are eminently qualified, highly respected lawyers who are dedicated to advancing racial equity and justice.

name: President Biden
tweet: Housing is infrastructure.  Broadband is infrastructure. Caregiving is infrastructure.   @SecFudge sat down to explain:  https://t.co/bY8TKqcrKG

name: President Biden
tweet: Businesses should know: they can provide paid time off for vaccines without a hit to their bottom line. That’s the American Rescue Plan at work. Go to  https://t.co/4yb5uVon5x to learn more.  https://t.co/ZKFICmzr88

name: President Biden
tweet: America’s national parks are irreplaceable treasures. They amaze us, inspire us, fill us with pride, and belong to all of us in equal measure. This National Park Week, I want to hear about your favorite memory at one of our national parks. Share by replying to this tweet.  https://t.co/oI7xXpUCQd

name: President Biden
tweet: Yesterday, Vice President Harris and I met with leaders of the Congressional Hispanic Caucus in the Oval Office. From achieving vaccine equity to passing immigration reform — we’re committed to working together to make progress on our shared goals and priorities.  https://t.co/A02iuPhXgO

name: President Biden
tweet: I believe everyone who wants a vaccine should be able to get one. Today I announced a tax credit made possible by the American Rescue Plan to help employers offer paid leave to workers getting vaccinated. Go to  https://t.co/4yb5uVon5x to learn more.

name: President Biden
tweet: My Administration is working around the clock to get America vaccinated as quickly as possible. Tune in as I deliver an update on our progress and the state of vaccinations.  https://t.co/jxOtlPOzsW

name: President Biden
tweet: The guilty verdict does not bring back George Floyd. But through the family’s pain, they are finding purpose so George’s legacy will not be just about his death, but about what we must do in his memory.  https://t.co/swjH0yprjN

name: President Biden
tweet: We can and we must do more to reduce the likelihood that tragedies like this will ever happen or occur again. To ensure that Black and Brown people — or anyone — don’t fear interactions with law enforcement.  https://t.co/z2VV09gtKf

name: President Biden
tweet: This can be a giant step forward in the march toward justice in America.  https://t.co/IUjvgxZfaT

name: President Biden
tweet: This can be a moment of significant change.

name: President Biden
tweet: “I can’t breathe.”   Those were George Floyd’s last words.   We cannot let them die with him. We have to keep hearing them.   We must not turn away. We cannot turn away.

name: President Biden
tweet: There’s meaningful police reform legislation in George Floyd’s name, but it shouldn’t take a year to get it done.   I assured the Floyd family that we’re going to continue to fight for the passage of the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act so I can sign it into law right away.

name: President Biden
tweet: No one should be above the law.   Today’s verdict sends that message, but it is not enough. We can’t stop here.   In order to deliver real change and reform, we can and we must do more to reduce the likelihood that tragedies like this ever occur.

name: President Biden
tweet: Today, a jury in Minnesota found former Minneapolis Police Officer Derek Chauvin guilty of murdering George Floyd.   The verdict is a step forward.   And while nothing can ever bring George Floyd back, this can be a giant step forward on the march towards justice in America.

name: President Biden
tweet: Please join me and the Vice President as we deliver remarks on the verdict in the trial of Derek Chauvin.  https://t.co/gE87hnPyVp

name: President Biden
tweet: This afternoon, I’m touring the Proterra electric battery manufacturing facility in South Carolina. Tune in.  https://t.co/34DeLFM75v

name: President Biden
tweet: The U.S.-Japanese alliance is stronger than ever.  https://t.co/XLkpaA5CkU

name: President Biden
tweet: It’s with great sadness that Jill and I learned of the passing of Vice President Walter Mondale, but great gratitude that we were able to call one of our nation’s most dedicated patriots and public servants a dear friend and mentor. Our hearts go out to the Mondale family.

name: President Biden
tweet: Today, I brought together Members of Congress for a discussion on the American Jobs Plan. These members are all former governors and mayors, so they understand the issues at stake firsthand. I’m confident that together, we’ll be able to rebuild our nation’s infrastructure.  https://t.co/AFMQ02Qp9N

name: President Biden
tweet: Today, the Ingenuity Mars Helicopter achieved liftoff — becoming the first aircraft to fly on another planet. NASA proved once again that with relentless determination and the power of America’s best minds, anything is possible.  https://t.co/elC4KPgSOL

name: President Biden
tweet: Thanks for tuning into last night’s Roll Up Your Sleeves special. Today, every American 16+ is eligible to get a COVID-19 vaccine. It’s free. It’s safe, and it’s how we’re going to bring this pandemic to an end. Get your vaccine.  https://t.co/raYdnl8bxF

name: President Biden
tweet: Everyone 16 and older in America is eligible for the shot today. Go and get ‘em, folks.

name: President Biden
tweet: From roads and bridges to high-speed internet and caregiving — the American Jobs Plan covers a lot of ground. So, I asked @SecretaryPete to break things down:  https://t.co/8NNqeykbch

name: President Biden
tweet: As of today, every American is eligible to receive the COVID-19 vaccine. For yourself, your neighbors, and your family — please, get your vaccine.  https://t.co/o75JYpGe6r

name: President Biden
tweet: Let me be clear: Every American has a right to clean drinking water. The American Jobs Plan will finally make that a reality by replacing 100% of America’s lead pipes and service lines.

name: President Biden
tweet: Imagine a future where we lead the world and tackle the threat of climate change with American jobs and ingenuity.  We can make that future a reality with the American Jobs Plan.  https://t.co/JcraqYmsjz

name: President Biden
tweet: Wear a mask. Stay socially distanced. Wash your hands. Get vaccinated.   Now is not the time to let up in the battle against COVID-19 — we have to fight this to the end.

name: President Biden
tweet: We can’t just build back to the way things were before the pandemic — we need to reimagine and build a new American economy.

name: President Biden
tweet: Our nation’s caregivers have been undervalued for far too long — and it’s time they receive the pay and benefits they deserve. I sat down with Susie from Texas to discuss how the American Jobs Plan will help caregivers like her.  https://t.co/V2jhtiS7PN

name: President Biden
tweet: I was honored to welcome Prime Minister Suga to the White House today as we usher in a new era of friendship between the U.S. and Japan. Both Pacific nations, we are also united by our shared commitment to the universal values of freedom, democracy, and human rights.  https://t.co/QJgbjNnceE

name: President Biden
tweet: Prime Minister Suga — Thank you for making the long trip to Washington, it was a pleasure to host you at the White House. I know we’ll be seeing a lot more of each other in the years to come as we work side by side to ensure a free and open Indo-Pacific region.

name: President Biden
tweet: I just wrapped up my first in-person bilateral meeting as president with Japanese Prime Minister Suga. Tune in as we hold a joint press conference.  https://t.co/0qDrhSod5f

name: President Biden
tweet: Vice President Harris and I have been briefed on the mass shooting at a FedEx facility in Indianapolis. God bless the eight individuals we lost and their loved ones, and we pray for the wounded for their recovery.   We can, and must, do more to reduce gun violence and save lives.

name: President Biden
tweet: I’m looking forward to welcoming my friend Prime Minister Suga to the White House this afternoon for the first foreign leader visit of my presidency — and to renewing the historic alliance between the United States and Japan.

name: President Biden
tweet: Equal pay is about justice, fairness, and who we are as a nation — and it makes all of us stronger. I’m glad the House passed the Paycheck Fairness Act to help close the gender pay gap — and I urge the Senate to swiftly do the same.

name: President Biden
tweet: This afternoon, Vice President Harris and I met with Congressional Asian Pacific American Caucus leaders in the Oval Office. We doubled down on our commitment to combat anti-Asian hate and discussed working together on everything from the American Jobs Plan to immigration.  https://t.co/RkPbvdGVOZ

name: President Biden
tweet: Thank you @GovMurphy for stepping up and taking action to save lives. It’s long past time we pass common-sense gun reforms in every corner of the country to end our gun violence epidemic.

name: President Biden
tweet: This afternoon, I’m delivering remarks on the new sanctions the United States is imposing on Russia. Tune in.  https://t.co/p17h2rnL0t

name: President Biden
tweet: Right now, the United States ranks 13th in the world in infrastructure — but we have the power to change that. The American Jobs Plan will modernize our roads, fix our bridges, invest in public transportation, and make our infrastructure more resilient to climate change.

name: President Biden
tweet: There are a lot of myths out there about the American Jobs Plan — so I asked @SecGranholm to clear a few things up.  https://t.co/FangHOgn49

name: President Biden
tweet: When we’ve invested in innovation throughout our history, we’ve been rewarded in extraordinary ways.  We have that opportunity once again.  https://t.co/NI5JysMQbY

name: President Biden
tweet: I am immeasurably grateful for the bravery that members of our Armed Forces have shown through nearly two decades of combat and deployments in Afghanistan. They have never backed down. They have never wavered in their resolve. And they have paid a tremendous price on our behalf.  https://t.co/nbUEir0Wil

name: President Biden
tweet: Our diplomacy does not hinge on having U.S. boots in harm’s way.   We have to change that thinking.

name: President Biden
tweet: I am now the fourth American president to preside over an American troop presence in Afghanistan.  I will not pass this responsibility to a fifth.  https://t.co/OpZK1Na5KP

name: President Biden
tweet: We went to Afghanistan because of the horrific attacks on 9/11 that happened 20 years ago.  That cannot explain why we should remain there in 2021.  Rather than return to war with the Taliban, we have to focus on the challenges of the future.

name: President Biden
tweet: It is time to end America’s longest war.   It is time for American troops to come home from Afghanistan.

name: President Biden
tweet: This afternoon, I’m announcing the withdrawal of U.S. troops from Afghanistan and providing an update on the path forward. Watch live.  https://t.co/SPiLX24VdM

name: President Biden
tweet: In less than three months, we’ve more than tripled the number of daily vaccinations.  That’s progress.  https://t.co/7AbWiOIypk

name: President Biden
tweet: Today, the FDA and CDC recommended a pause in the use of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine. Here’s what you need to know:  https://t.co/QVtrEkqO8F

name: President Biden
tweet: Jill and I send our warmest wishes to the South Asian and Southeast Asian communities who are celebrating Vaisakhi, Navratri, Songkran, and the incoming New Year this week. Happy Bengali, Cambodian, Lao, Myanmarese, Nepali, Sinhalese, Tamil, Thai, and Vishu New Year!

name: President Biden
tweet: This can be the moment that America wins the future — but it’s going to take all of us to make it happen.  Let’s do big things, together.  https://t.co/gpLrVyli79

tweet: “When the will defies fear, when duty throws the gauntlet down to fate, when honor scorns to compromise with death — that is heroism.” — R.G. Ingersoll   Capitol Police Officer William Evans was a hero.  https://t.co/Xtius0vq0z

name: President Biden
tweet: Race should never determine health outcomes — and pregnancy and childbirth should be safe for all. But for too many Black women, safety and equity have been denied. This Black Maternal Health Week, our Administration is taking action to change that.  https://t.co/9s33KmLSdv

name: President Biden
tweet: We can’t let the divisions of the moment stop us from doing right by our future. That’s why this afternoon, I brought together a bipartisan group of lawmakers to discuss how we can build America’s infrastructure back better with the American Jobs Plan.  https://t.co/OT3gSXQcU2

name: President Biden
tweet: As the crescent moon ushers in the month, Jill and I send our warmest greetings and best wishes to Muslim communities in the United States and around the world. Ramadan Kareem.

name: President Biden
tweet: Today I’m thinking about Daunte Wright and his family — and the pain, anger, and trauma that Black America experiences every day. While we await a full investigation, we know what we need to do to move forward: rebuild trust and ensure accountability so no one is above the law.

name: President Biden
tweet: When I served as Vice President, I asked to be the last person with the President before big decisions were made — and @VP is providing the same counsel to me. She’s the last voice in the room and never fails to speak the truth as we work to build our nation back better.  https://t.co/I4EXm204l3

name: President Biden
tweet: It’s time we invest in the future of America once again.

name: President Biden
tweet: Our progress on vaccinations is proof that there’s nothing America can’t achieve when we do it together.  https://t.co/51fKUzciVJ

name: President Biden
tweet: Gun violence in this country is an epidemic — and it’s long past time Congress take action.

name: President Biden
tweet: This isn’t complicated.  https://t.co/4Fei10Vjih

name: President Biden
tweet: The American Jobs Plan is a once-in-a-generation opportunity to invest in the future of America. For this episode of our weekly conversation, I invited members of my Jobs Cabinet to break down their favorite parts.  https://t.co/Kyn0lEmVW1

name: President Biden
tweet: A new study put out just last week found that at least 55 of our largest corporations used various loopholes to pay $0 in federal income taxes in 2020.  It’s not fair to the rest of the American taxpayers — and we’re going to put an end to it.

name: President Biden
tweet: High-speed internet is essential infrastructure in the 21st century.  https://t.co/1vAeHdAUQ2

name: President Biden
tweet: I’m excited to share my official portrait — and honored to serve as your president every day.  https://t.co/JIe5mDJK5a

name: President Biden
tweet: Universal background checks are supported by the vast majority of Americans — and the majority of gun owners.  So let’s be clear, this is not a partisan issue. It’s an American issue.

name: President Biden
tweet: Prince Philip’s legacy will live on not only through his family, but in all the charitable endeavors he shaped. Jill and I are keeping the Queen and Prince Philip’s children, grandchildren, great-grandchildren, and the people of the United Kingdom in our hearts during this time.

name: President Biden
tweet: I know that the conversation about guns in this country can be a difficult one. But even here, there’s much more common ground than some would have us believe.  https://t.co/ZtN0Zr0rBf

name: President Biden
tweet: We need to ban assault weapons and high-capacity magazines in this country.   There’s no reason somebody needs a weapon of war with 100 rounds in a magazine. None.

tweet: We need more than “thoughts and prayers” from Congress. It’s time to act.  https://t.co/BT4VQlyYsD

name: President Biden
tweet: On this Holocaust Remembrance Day, we remember the precious lives we lost and honor those who survived to bear witness. We must all give anti-Semitism and hate no safe harbor and ensure the atrocities of the Holocaust never occur again.

name: President Biden
tweet: The Senate should immediately pass the three House-passed bills to close loopholes in the gun background check system.  That is one of the best tools we have right now to prevent gun violence and save lives.

name: President Biden
tweet: My Administration is taking initial steps to reduce gun violence, including:  - Stopping the proliferation of ghost guns - Regulating pistols modified with a stabilizing brace - Helping states adopt red flag laws - Supporting community violence interventions

name: President Biden
tweet: Today, I’m joining Vice President Harris and Attorney General Garland to announce new actions to reduce gun violence. Tune in.  https://t.co/p6dgJRYKwe

name: President Biden
tweet: Whatever partisan divisions there are around other issues — there don’t have to be on infrastructure.  We’re one nation — united and connected.  https://t.co/oSdugebDuc

name: President Biden
tweet: It’s time we focus on our nation’s caregiving infrastructure — the kind of infrastructure that helps people build a better life and carve out their place in the middle class.  https://t.co/B91j2Pj4kQ

tweet: We need to start seeing infrastructure through the eyes of working people.  https://t.co/ohYa2PBsOr

name: President Biden
tweet: Two hundred years ago trains weren’t “traditional” infrastructure either — until America made the choice to lay the tracks.

name: President Biden
tweet: The idea of infrastructure has always evolved to meet the aspirations of the American people — and it’s evolving again today.  https://t.co/AgJAdN4HML

name: President Biden
tweet: We are America.   We don’t just fix for today.   We build for tomorrow.

name: President Biden
tweet: Above all, infrastructure is about meeting the needs of the nation and putting Americans to work to get the job done.

name: President Biden
tweet: This afternoon, I’m delivering remarks on the historic infrastructure investments in the American Jobs Plan. Tune in.  https://t.co/oxOiRtLI8C

name: President Biden
tweet: This afternoon, I stopped by a vaccination clinic at the Virginia Theological Seminary. It’s America at its best.  https://t.co/iiT8r1OVnp

name: President Biden
tweet: According to the latest CDC data, almost 80 percent of pre-K through 12 teachers, school staff, and childcare workers received at least one shot by the end of March. That is great progress in protecting our educators – our essential workers.
